Column 1
-----------------------------------------------------------------------

### Duration by Month Hours
```{r}
consults %>% 
  select(Date = `Start Date`, Duration = `Duration in minutes`) %>% 
  mutate(Month = month(Date, label = TRUE, abbr = TRUE)) %>% 
  group_by(Month) %>% 
  summarise(Total = sum(Duration)/60) %>% 
  mutate(mon2 = factor(Month, 
                        levels = c("Sep", "Oct", "Nov", "Dec", 
                                   "Jan", "Feb", "Mar", "Apr"),
                        labels = c("Sep \'16", "Oct", "Nov", "Dec", 
                                   "Jan \'17", "Feb", "Mar", "Apr"))) %>% 
  ggvis(~mon2, ~Total) %>% 
  layer_bars() %>% 
  add_axis("x", title = "Month" , 
           properties = axis_props(grid = list(stroke = "white"))
           ) %>% 
  add_axis("y", title = "Total Consult Hours",
           properties = axis_props(grid = list(stroke = "white"))
           )


```

Column 1
-----------------------------------------------------------------------

### Consult Minutes by Type 

```{r treemapify}
consults_treemap <- consults %>% 
  mutate(Primary2 = `Primary Question Type`) %>% 
  select(`Primary Question Type`, Primary2, Minutes = `Duration in minutes`) %>% 
  mutate(Primary2 = str_split_fixed(Primary2, "\\(", 2)[,1]) %>% 
  group_by(Primary2) %>% 
  summarise(Minutes = sum(Minutes)) %>% 
  arrange(-Minutes) %>% 
  mutate(Type = Primary2) %>% 
  mutate(Type = gsub("Data\\s", "", Type)) %>% 
  mutate(Type = str_to_title(Type)) %>% 
  mutate(Type = if_else(Type == "Gis", "GIS", Type)) %>% 
  mutate(freq = desc(Minutes))

ggplot(consults_treemap, aes(fill = freq,
                      label = Type,
#                      subgroup = Primary2,
                      area = Minutes)) +
  geom_treemap() +
  geom_treemap_text(
    fontface = "italic",
    colour = "white",
    place = "centre",
    grow = TRUE
  )
```


### Duration Hours by Researcher Status
```{r}
consults %>% 
  select(Date = `Start Date`, Status = `Researcher Status`, Duration = `Duration in minutes`) %>% 
  group_by(Status) %>% 
  summarise(Hours = round(sum(Duration) / 60, 1)) %>% 
  # arrange(-Hours) %>% 
  mutate(Status = factor(Status,
                          levels = c("Graduate Student","Undergraduate", "Faculty", "Staff",
                                     "Other", "Library Staff (Duke)", 
                                     "Library Staff Outside Duke", "Postdoc", "Alumni"),
                          labels = c("Grad",  "Ugrad", "Fac", "Staff", "Other", 
                                     "Library-Duke", "Library", "Postdoc", "Alumni"))) %>% 
  # count(`Location/Format`, sort = TRUE)
  ggvis(~Status, ~Hours) %>% 
  layer_bars() %>% 
  set_options(height = "100%", width="100%") %>%
  add_axis("x", title = "" , 
           properties = axis_props(grid = list(stroke = "white"))
           ) %>% 
  add_axis("y", title = "",
           properties = axis_props(grid = list(stroke = "white"))
           ) 
```


Column 2
-----------------------------------------------------------------------

### Hours by Department

```{r}

Consults_Total_Minutes <- consults %>% 
  summarise(Total_Minutes = sum(`Duration in minutes`)) 

Consults_by_Department <- consults %>% 
  select(Department = `Subject(s)`, Duration = `Duration in minutes`) %>% 
  group_by(Department) %>% 
  summarise(Minutes = sum(Duration)) %>% 
  arrange(-Minutes)

multidiscipline_category_minutes <- Consults_by_Department %>% 
  filter(grepl(';',`Department`)) %>% # select the rows which have multiple disciplines, as noted by the presence of a semi-colon
  summarise(Minutes = sum(Minutes)) 

multidiscipline_no <- Consults_by_Department %>% 
  filter(!grepl(';', Department)) # select the rows which do not have multiple disciplines, as noted by the presence of a semi-colon

Departments_with_multiD <- bind_rows(multidiscipline_no, 
          data_frame(Department = "Multiple Disciplines", 
                     Minutes = multidiscipline_category_minutes[[1]]))

Consults_by_Department <- Departments_with_multiD %>% 
  arrange(-Minutes) %>% 
  mutate(Percent = round(Minutes / Consults_Total_Minutes[[1]], 3) * 100) %>% 
  mutate(Hours = round(Minutes / 60, 2)) %>% 
  select(Department, Hours, Percent) 

datatable(Consults_by_Department, extensions="Scroller", 
          style="bootstrap", class="compact", width="100%", 
          options=list(deferRender=TRUE,  scrollY=300, scroller=TRUE))
```

### Researcher Status: Consult Frequency and Consult Hours

```{r}

consult_n <- consults %>% 
  select(Date = `Start Date`, Status = `Researcher Status`, Duration = `Duration in minutes`) %>% 
  group_by(Status) %>% 
  summarise(Hours = round(sum(Duration) / 60)) %>% 
  arrange(-Hours) %>% 
  mutate(Status = factor(Status,
                          levels = c("Graduate Student","Undergraduate", "Faculty", "Staff",
                                     "Other", "Library Staff (Duke)", 
                                     "Library Staff Outside Duke", "Postdoc", "Alumni"),
                          labels = c("Grad",  "Ugrad", "Fac", "Staff", "Other", 
                                     "Library-Duke", "Library", "Postdoc", "Alumni"))) %>% 
  select(Status, Value = Hours) %>% 
  mutate(Type = "Hours")


consult_hours <- consults %>%
  select(Status = `Researcher Status`) %>% 
  count(Status, sort = TRUE) %>% 
  mutate(Status = factor(Status),
         levels = c("Graduate Student","Undergraduate", "Faculty", "Staff",
                    "Other", "Library Staff (Duke)", 
                    "Library Staff Outside Duke", "Postdoc", "Alumni"),
         labels = c("Grad",  "Ugrad", "Fac", "Staff", "Other", 
                    "Library-Duke", "Library", "Postdoc", "Alumni")) %>% 
  select(Status = labels, Value = n) %>% 
  mutate(Type = "n")

compare <- bind_rows(consult_n, consult_hours) 

ggplot(compare, aes(x = Status, y = Value, 
                    fill = factor(Type, levels = c("Hours", "n")))) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", position = "dodge") +
  scale_x_discrete(limits=c("Alumni", "Postdoc", "Library", 
                            "Library-Duke", "Other", "Staff",
                            "Fac", "Ugrad", "Grad")) +
  scale_fill_brewer(name = "Consults",
                    type = "qual",
                    palette = 1,
                    labels = c("Hours", "Number")) +
  coord_flip()


```

### Consult Types: Consult Frequency and Consult Hours
```{r}

consults_type_numb <- consults %>% 
  mutate(Primary2 = `Primary Question Type`) %>% 
  select(`Primary Question Type`, Primary2) %>% 
  mutate(Primary2 = str_split_fixed(Primary2, "\\(", 2)[,1]) %>% 
  count(Primary2, sort = TRUE) %>% 
  mutate(Type = Primary2) %>% 
  mutate(Type = gsub("Data\\s", "", Type)) %>% 
  mutate(Type = str_to_title(Type)) %>% 
  mutate(Type = if_else(Type == "Gis", "GIS", Type)) %>% 
  mutate(Category = "n") %>% 
  rename(Value = n)




consults_type_hours <- consults %>% 
  mutate(Primary2 = `Primary Question Type`) %>% 
  select(`Primary Question Type`, Primary2, Minutes = `Duration in minutes`) %>% 
  mutate(Primary2 = str_split_fixed(Primary2, "\\(", 2)[,1]) %>% 
  group_by(Primary2) %>% 
  summarise(Hours = round(sum(Minutes) / 60)) %>% 
  arrange(-Hours) %>% 
  mutate(Type = Primary2) %>% 
  mutate(Type = gsub("Data\\s", "", Type)) %>% 
  mutate(Type = str_to_title(Type)) %>% 
  mutate(Type = if_else(Type == "Gis", "GIS", Type)) %>% 
  rename(Value = Hours) %>% 
  mutate(Category = "Hours")



compare_type <- bind_rows(consults_type_numb, consults_type_hours) 

ggplot(compare_type, aes(x = Type, y = Value, 
                    fill = factor(Category, levels = c("Hours", "n")))) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", position = "dodge") +
  scale_x_discrete(limits=c("Management", "Cleaning", "Other", 
                            "Analysis", "Sources", "GIS",
                            "Visualization")) +
  scale_fill_brewer(name = "Consults",
                    type = "qual",
                    palette = 1,
                    labels = c("Hours", "Number")) +
  coord_flip()
```

Column 1

### Departments:  Consult frequency and Consult Hours
```{r}

consults_total <- consults %>% 
  count()

# Caculate Frequency of Departmental Consults

Departments <- consults %>%
  count(`Subject(s)`, sort = TRUE) 

multidiscipline_category <- Departments %>% 
  filter(grepl(';',`Subject(s)`)) %>% # select the rows which have multiple disciplines, as noted by the presence of a semi-colon
  count()

multidiscipline_category <- multidiscipline_category[[1]]

multidiscipline_no <- Departments %>% 
  filter(!grepl(';',`Subject(s)`)) # select the rows which do not have multiple disciplines, as noted by the presence of a semi-colon

Departments_with_multiD <- bind_rows(multidiscipline_no, 
          data_frame(`Subject(s)` = "Multiple Disciplines", 
                     n = multidiscipline_category[[1]])
)

Consults_by_Department_no <- Departments_with_multiD %>% 
  arrange(-n) %>% 
  mutate(Percent = round(n / consults_total[[1]], 3) * 100) %>% 
  rename(Department = `Subject(s)`) %>% 
  mutate(Category = "n") %>% 
  select(Department, Percent, Category) %>% 
  top_n(15, Percent)  

# Calculate Departmental Consults by Hours
Consults_Total_Minutes <- consults %>% 
  summarise(Total_Minutes = sum(`Duration in minutes`)) 

Consults_by_Department <- consults %>% 
  select(Department = `Subject(s)`, Duration = `Duration in minutes`) %>% 
  group_by(Department) %>% 
  summarise(Minutes = sum(Duration)) %>% 
  arrange(-Minutes) 

multidiscipline_category_minutes <- Consults_by_Department %>% 
  filter(grepl(';',`Department`)) %>% # select the rows which have multiple disciplines, as noted by the presence of a semi-colon
  summarise(Minutes = sum(Minutes)) 

multidiscipline_no <- Consults_by_Department %>% 
  filter(!grepl(';', Department)) %>% # select the rows which do not have multiple disciplines, as noted by the presence of a semi-colon
  mutate(Category = "Hours")

Departments_with_multiD <- bind_rows(multidiscipline_no, 
          data_frame(Department = "Multiple Disciplines", 
                     Minutes = multidiscipline_category_minutes[[1]],
                     Category = "Hours"))

Consults_by_Department_hours <- Departments_with_multiD %>% 
  arrange(-Minutes) %>% 
  mutate(Percent = round(Minutes / Consults_Total_Minutes[[1]], 3) * 100) %>% 
  mutate(Hours = round(Minutes / 60, 2)) %>% 
  select(Department, Percent, Category) %>% 
  top_n(15, Percent)
  
```

```{r}
Department_hours_n_combined <- bind_rows(Consults_by_Department_no, Consults_by_Department_hours) 

ggplot(Department_hours_n_combined, aes(x = reorder(Department, Percent), y = Percent, 
                    fill = factor(Category, levels = c("Hours", "n")))) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", position = "dodge") +
  scale_fill_brewer(name = "Consults",
                    type = "qual",
                    palette = 1,
                    labels = c("Hours", "Number")) +
  labs(xlab("Departments")) +
  coord_flip()
```
